Differentiating $\dfrac{1}{(1-x)^{2}} = \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}n\,x^{n-1}$:
\[
 \frac{2}{(1-x)^{3}} = \sum_{n=2}^{\infty}n(n-1)x^{n-2}
 = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(n+2)(n+1)x^{n}
\]
for $|x| < 1$.

From Example [ex:ps-diff-geom], $\dfrac{1}{(1-x)^{2}} = \displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(n+1)x^{n}$.

Multiplying by $x$:
\[
 \frac{x}{(1-x)^{2}} = x\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(n+1)x^{n}
 = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(n+1)x^{n+1}
 = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}n\,x^{n}
 = x + 2x^{2} + 3x^{3} + \cdots
\]
for $|x| < 1$.

